cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.KR, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper discusses the development of explanation capabilities for rule-based expert systems managing imprecise and uncertain knowledge, which falls under the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of possibility theory and max-min algebra also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.KR). Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) due to the use of equations in max-min algebra.
